# Proppy Core Rules

## Tech Stack

Frontend: in property-landing folder
- Next.js (App Router) + Tailwind
- Mobile-first

Backend: in proppy-backend
- Django REST Framework (DRF)
- Always filter data by company (multi-tenant)

- KISS (no overengineering)
- Mobile-first (Tailwind)
- UI in components
- Logic in hooks
- No API calls in components
- No hardcoded colors (use globals.css)
- Use TypeScript (no any)
- Dark and light theme

## Workflow
- Finish feature before changing approach
- Do not refactor mid-feature
- Reuse existing code first
- Ask if unclear (do not guess)

## Code Explanation (IMPORTANT)
- After EVERY new component or function, add a SHORT comment block explaining:
  - What it does (1 sentence)
  - Why it exists (1 sentence)
  - What would break if removed
- Use inline comments for any logic that isn't obvious
- If a pattern is used (e.g. controlled form, modal wrapper), name it and explain it once

## Teaching Rules
- I am a Next.js beginner — never assume I know why something is done
- When introducing a new concept or pattern, explain it in 1-2 sentences before the code
- If there are two ways to do something, briefly say why you chose this one
- Flag anything I should learn more about with a // LEARN: comment

## KISS Enforcement
- If a solution needs more than ~50 lines, stop and ask if we can simplify
- Prefer boring, readable code over clever code
- One file = one responsibility, no exceptions
- If you're creating a new abstraction, justify it first — do not just do it

## Output
- Return working code only
- Keep components small
